 <H1>Indexes</H1> 
 <P><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>An index on a file speeds up selections on the search key fields for the index.
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Any subset of the fields of a relation can be the search key for an index on the relation.
<LI>Search key is not the same as key (minimal set of fields that uniquely identify a record in a relation).
</UL></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>An index contains a collection of data entries, and supports efficient retrieval of all data entries k* with a given key value k.</H2></P>

